AIR HOCKEY
-----------
This simple game is based on the arcade game of the same name. Your ultimate goal is gain the highest score, by using your paddle (mallet) to hit the puck into the opponent's goal (in red). Your opponent has a mallet of his own, that can deflect the puck as well. It will also try to score.


HOW TO USE IT
-------------
To start, click "setup". This will create the air hockey table, mallets, and puck. To start playing, click "go" and move your mouse cursor inside the playing area. Your cursor will now control your mallet. Move your mallet towards the puck to hit it. When the puck goes inside the opponent's goal, you will score a point, and the puck will again be in the center. 


KNOWN BUGS
----------
Sometimes, when running the model, this sudden runtime error appears:

	"error while turtle 1 running OF in procedure BOUNCE
 	called by procedure GO
	OF expected input to be a turtle agentset or patch agentset or turtle or patch 			but got NOBODY instead."

This usually happens when the model is running without the mouse cursor inside the viewing area.

